# UI Restyle Guidelines

When redesigning tabs, panels, list items, or controls in StatsClient:

## Corner radius — restrained, not bubbly

Avoid making everything heavily rounded. Too much roundness reads as playful / “kids app”, not a professional dental lab tool.

| Element | Prefer | Avoid |
|---------|--------|-------|
| Cards / panels | `CornerRadius="8"`–`10` | `14`–`18` on every surface |
| Buttons / inputs | `CornerRadius="6"`–`8` | Pill-shaped everything |
| Small chips / tags | `CornerRadius="4"`–`6` | Large pill badges |
| Dropdown popups | `CornerRadius="8"`–`10` | Oversized soft bubbles |

Use **one** rounded layer per visual group (e.g. outer card rounded; inner fields slightly less or square).

## Tone

- Pastel / glass is fine — keep it **clean and calm**, not cute.
- Prefer subtle borders and light shadows over thick glows and bouncy hover.
- Preserve existing color semantics (converters, age/status strokes, category accents).

## When touching existing redesigned screens

If restyling something that already uses high radius (e.g. `14`–`16`), **tone it down** as part of the change unless the user says otherwise.
